@wbangcaHD @PeterSchiff Dogecoin is the https://t.co/SwcbCZXCEP of Crypto. Stick with Bitcoin & Ethereum, the Amazon & Google of Crypto. #Bitcoin https://t.co/1cmw0rPhDr

@BillyM2k @BigImpactHumans @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan I see a robust community of people that advocate buying Dogecoin & hoping that Elon Musk will say or do something that makes everyone rich. But, I am not seeing a lot of people advocating how Dogecoin can compete & win as a feature rich asset in the Crypto Revolution.

@BigImpactHumans @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan I was looking at Dogecoin on GitHub and it did not appear to have a large software development community, or a lot of software development activity. Where can I find the robust community that you mention?

@UFMJA @Iamhowarddanny @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan And, Dogecoin was created as a meme & parody coin. But, now it has this amazing opportunity to become a core foundational cryptocurrency. But, “What got it here won’t get it there” so it needs to reset a bit. Or, maybe it has already done that. That is what I am trying to learn.

@BillyM2k @Iamhowarddanny @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan As you likely know, there is tremendous venture capital pouring in to Bitcoin & Ethereum. Are you seeing the same for Dogecoin? If so, that is fantastic.

@Iamhowarddanny @UFMJA @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan I do believe that nations & corporations will have their own cryptocurrencies. It could be that Tesla or some country adopts Dogecoin as the basis of their Crypto strategy. This would be more efficient than building a net new Crypto from scratch.

@Iamhowarddanny @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan I agree. And, then the next question is what features & ecosystem partners does Dogecoin need to achieve this role. And, can Dogecoin recruit the software developers required to execute that strategy.

@UFMJA @BillyM2k @Iamhowarddanny @BarrySilbert @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Dogecoin & Bitcoin can absolutely co-exist and complement each other. They can win together. But, I would say that the Dogecoin leaders need to come forward to evolve & advance their vision from meme coin to a core participant in the Crypto Revolution.

@Iamhowarddanny @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Amazon was a winner in the Internet Revolution because it had the best software developers & the best partner ecosystem. Similarly the Crypto Revolution will be won based on who has the best software developers & ecosystems. If Dogecoin has the best developers then it will win.

@Iamhowarddanny @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan What is the Dogecoin vision? Where will Dogecoin be in 20 years? Will it be the https://t.co/SwcbCZXCEP of the Crypto Revolution? Or, will it be the Amazon or Google of the Crypto Revolution? Why do people buy it or invest in it?

@BillyM2k @username_Dizzy @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Bitcoin is the same thing, but with digital scarcity, a robust developer & mining community, and a robust ecosystem being built on top of it. These are significant differences. How can you suggest that Dogecoin & Bitcoin are “literally the same”?

@mochafro @TotallyYumbo @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan I agree that Dogecoin is fun & great for learning about cryptocurrencies. You can buy some Dogecoin, spend it, watch it, and begin to explore other cryptocurrencies.

@ClayLambert20 @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @WayneVaughan I am not rooting against Dogecoin or any cryptocurrency. If the Dogecoin developers & mining community are coming together then that is fantastic. But, what is the vision & what are the use cases for a cryptocurrency that mints 14 Million new coins per day?

@TotallyYumbo @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Dogecoin barely has 1000 nodes securing it. It will likely suffer a 51% attack soon after this bull run. At that point the Dogecoin ledger might be rebased on Ethereum so that the Dogecoin fans can continue to have fun. #Dogecoin

@TotallyYumbo @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Dogecoin’s issues are less about the “technical aspects” and more about it’s lack of a developer & miner community. As you suggest, Crypto is still in its infancy. Thus the cryptocurrencies with the strongest developer & miner communities will be in position to win.

@TotallyYumbo @BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Dogecoin is not an emerging technology. Dogecoin is a point-in-time copy of Litecoin, which was a copy of Bitcoin. Bitcoin is the emerging technology that is rapidly evolving across a number of dimensions. #Bitcoin #Dogecoin

@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan When you invest in a cryptocurrency you are investing in a vision, strategy, developer community, mining community, & ecosystem. Bitcoin & Ethereum have robust evolving communities. Dogecoin is part joke & part Get Rich Quick scheme. How can you advocate investing in Dogecoin?

@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan There are 19 Million Bitcoin in circulation. There are 130 Billion Dogecoin in circulation, with 14 Million new Dogecoin mined per day. If they “have practically the same use case” then why is there a gigantic difference in their supply levels? #Bitcoin

@BillyM2k @BarrySilbert @UFMJA @ClayLambert20 @WayneVaughan Dogecoin is the https://t.co/SwcbCZXCEP of the Crypto Revolution. It will ultimately go back to zero. Dogecoin was created as a joke and the joke is being perpetuated today. It has zero vision, next to zero developers, and a near infinite supply. https://t.co/BwixsmugYx
